The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 December is 143,697 (16,561.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 December, there were 9,513 new confirmed cases (1,096.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 December, there were 6,846 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 39% (2,667 extra cases).
